t-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;" target="_blank">约翰尼·赖特 (Johnny Wright) (@wright7680) 分享的帖子</a></p></div></blockquote><p><script async src="//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js"></script></p><p></p><p>在音乐会之前，汀布莱克的律师埃德·伯克还<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/justin-timberlake-refused-breathalyser-when-arrested-for-driving-while-intoxicated-his-lawyer-says-3766720">声称这位歌手拒绝了呼吸测试</a>：“这项指控是一项单一罪名，因为他拒绝了呼气测试。汀布莱克先生还被指控另外两项法庭传票，即闯停车标志和未在正确的车道上行驶。据<a href="https://www.tmz.com/2024/06/18/justin-timberlake-arrested-police-custody-new-york/#continued" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>TMZ</em></a>报道，这位前<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/n-sync" target="_blank" rel="noopener">*NSYNC</a>明星将于 7 月 26 日重返法庭。</p><p>在其他地方，据报道<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/cop-who-arrested-justin-timberlake-reportedly-didnt-recognise-him-star-said-it-would-ruin-his-tour-3766825">逮捕汀布莱克的警察据称不认识这位流行歌星</a>，汀布莱克据称称这会“毁掉”他的巡演。一位消息人士向<a href="https://pagesix.com/2024/06/18/entertainment/justin-timberlake-once-admitted-to-getting-completely-plastered-doing-his-fair-share-of-drugs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>《第六页》</em></a>透露：“贾斯汀低声说道，‘这会毁掉巡演。’警察回答说：“什么旅行？”贾斯汀说，‘世界巡演。’” </p><figure id="attachment_3766894" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3766894" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3766894" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Justin-Timberlake-2024.jpg" alt="贾斯汀·汀布莱克（摄影：Axelle/Bauer-Griffin/FilmMagic）" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Justin-Timberlake-2024.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Justin-Timberlake-2024-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Justin-Timberlake-2024-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Justin-Timberlake-2024-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Justin-Timberlake-2024-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Justin-Timberlake-2024-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3766894" class="wp-caption-text">贾斯汀·汀布莱克（摄影：Axelle/Bauer-Griffin/FilmMagic）</figcaption></figure><p>汀布莱克最近发行了他的第六张专辑《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/justin-timberlake-everything-i-thought-it-was-review-sullied-superstar-gets-trapped-in-the-typical-3601736">Everything I Thought It Was</a> 》。 <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/justin-timberlake-everything-i-thought-it-was-review-sullied-superstar-gets-trapped-in-the-typical-3601736"><em>《NME》</em>在一篇三星级评论中写道</a>：“汀布莱克在一首定义时代的 NSYNC 热门歌曲中演唱了《It&#39;s gone be may》25 年后，成为了一位不太受人喜爱的流行巨星。</p><p> “《我以为的一切》表明他并没有失去他的声线或节奏的能力，但这还不足以让你排除过去的轻罪。目前，汀布莱克这个充满问题的最爱时代还得等待。”</p><p>这位歌手将于下周（6 月 25 日至 26 日）在纽约麦迪逊广场花园表演两场演出。 <a href="https://ticketmaster.evyy.net/c/2862475/264167/4272?sharedid=NME&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ticketmaster.com%2Fjustin-timberlake-tickets%2Fartist%2F847841" target="_blank" rel="noopener">请访问此处购买</a>最后一刻的门票。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/justin-timberlake-addresses-tough-week-at-first-concert-since-dui-arrest-3767827">贾斯汀·汀布莱克 (Justin Timberlake) 在酒后驾车被捕后的首场音乐会上谈到了“艰难的一周”，</a>这篇文章首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ;
